howto:
h1. Hello World Example
h2. Summary
This example shows the most basic usage of Terracotta. It shows a simple clustered POJO, which has a single integer field {{counter}}. The POJO has a main method, which invokes the {{run}} method on a singleton instance of the POJO. The singleton instance is declared as a root, which gives the POJO it's clustered ability via Terracotta.
h2. How to run
*Node 1:* {code} $ javac *.java $ start-tc-server & $ dso-java Main Counter is: 1 {code}
*Node 2:* {code} $ dso-java Main Counter is: 2 {code}
